    <briefdescription>
<para>This class provides a generic access to simd operations on x86, x86 AMD and ARM architectures. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Functionalities provided by the class are :<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>load vector size aligned data from memory (SimdGet)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>getting x[i-1] and x[i+1] for finite difference algorithms (SimdGetAtLeft, SimdGetAtRight, etc)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>arithmetic operations (+ - * /)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>conditional affectation (SimdSelect) See simd_malloc() and simd_free() to allocate aligned blocs of memory. </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
